4. Manual Vulnerability Testing (DVWA)

Security Level: Low

A. SQL Injection
Normal Input:
1

Malicious Input:
1' OR '1'='1

Result:

Multiple user records displayed

Confirms SQL Injection vulnerability

Cause:

No parameterized queries

Direct input embedding

B. Reflected XSS
Payload:
<script>alert('XSS')</script>

Result:

Alert box appeared

Cause:

No HTML escaping

Input reflected directly

C. Stored XSS
Payload:
<script>alert('Stored')</script>

Result:

Alert triggered on every page load

Risk:

Affects all users

Persistent attack

D. Command Injection
Normal Input:
127.0.0.1

Malicious Input:
127.0.0.1; ls

Result:

Directory listing displayed

Arbitrary command execution

Cause:

Unsanitized input passed to system command

